<dl id="n35253c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35253c">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35253c"> 253(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Figg Gladiator</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">One of <font color="green">[Madame Violante&apos;s]</font> company, Mr. Figg, &ldquo;the English gladiator,&rdquo; secured more popularity, and confided to the historian of the stage just mentioned, as an instance of his success, that he had not bought a shirt for more than twenty years, but had sold some dozens within that time. <small> J. Fitzgerald Molloy, <a name="JFMR2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JFMR2"><cite title="source">The Romance of the Irish Stage</cite></a> (1897) I 9</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
